Afrobeat singer Seun Kuti has revealed why poor Nigerians have no choice but to sell their votes ahead of the 2023 general election. According to a post on his Instagram page on Wednesday, Kuti stated that Nigerian professionals are responsible for the choice of the poor Nigerians as they have already sold their souls in the name of ‘I’m doing my job. Kuti said, “I hear one more ‘stop selling your votes’ directed at the poor by those who have already ‘sold their Souls’ I will snap. -Advertisement- “The reason why poor Nigerians have no choice but to sell their votes is that all, or at least most(99.9%) of Nigerian professionals have sold their souls in the name of ‘I’m doing my job.” “Journalists Judges lecturers Bankers Oil industry workers Farm owners Cattle rearer, Policeman, Soldiers, Civil Servants, Engineers, Accountants, etc have all sold their souls and are willing to carry out any wicked act in the name of ‘I’m doing my job’. “The job of destroying your country! Add musicians and actors.”